## 📂 Project Structure

The project follows a strict **Model-View-Controller (MVC)** architectural pattern:

```text
Sahayogi/
├── run.py                 # Application launcher & connection validator
├── config.py              # Central configuration loader (environment variables)
├── requirements.txt       # Python dependencies configuration
├── setup.py               # Interactive developer environment setup script
├── guide.md               # Prescriptive build rulebook & user story criteria
├── app/                   # Core application package
│   ├── __init__.py        # Application factory (`create_app`)
│   ├── database.py        # Centralized parameterized MySQL query connector
│   ├── auth.py            # Login/Admin role validation decorators
│   ├── models/            # Database query classes (BaseModel, User, Profile, etc.)
│   ├── controllers/       # Business logic (AuthController, AdminController, etc.)
│   ├── routes/            # Flask blueprints & routing definitions
│   ├── templates/         # UI templates (Jinja2 HTML layouts)
│   └── static/            # Static assets (vanilla CSS styles, JS files, uploads)
└── tests/                 # Full integration test suite
```

---

## 🛠️ CLI Commands Reference

Manage your local development instance with the following commands:

| Command | Description |
| :--- | :--- |
| `py setup.py` | Runs the full automated environment setup. |
| `py run.py` | Starts the Flask development server on `http://localhost:5000`. |
| `python -m flask --app run init-db` | Drops and recreates the MySQL schema tables. |
| `python -m flask --app run seed-reference-data` | Seeds base roles and the default admin user. |
| `python -m flask --app run elevate-user <email>` | Admin tool to promote a user account to the admin role. |
| `python -m flask --app run test-email <email>` | Tests SMTP settings or logs a dummy email to the local file. |
| `python -m pytest tests/` | Executes all integration tests. |
| `python -m pytest --cov=app tests/` | Runs tests and prints code coverage statistics. |

---

## 🛡️ Security, Privacy & Compliance (LESPI)

- **Authentication Guarding**: Critical actions (such as moderation, suspensions, and role adjustments) are secured at the route level via backend controllers. UI links are hidden, and unauthorized access throws a `403 Forbidden` error.
- **Lockout Protections**: Accounts are temporarily locked for **10 minutes** after **3 consecutive failed login attempts** to protect against brute-force attacks.
- **GDPR Rights**: Users have the right to permanently erase their profiles. Initiating account deletion requires password confirmation. Personal identifiers (name, email, avatar, etc.) are purged, and messages/reviews are anonymized to `Deleted User` to protect historical statistics.
- **Credit Security**: Transactions are checked at the controller level to prevent users from initiating exchanges without sufficient credits. No cash deposits are allowed.
- **Interactive Calling**: Real-time video calls use peer-to-peer **WebRTC signaling** via a MySQL signal pool. Stale sessions are automatically closed via heartbeats.
